column5: Monday January 28th, I headed on onto the river for the first time to try for some walleye through the ice.  What a morning it was, learning how to use the vexlarâ€¦yet I did manage one fish for my efforts.  It was a great time and the weather was perfect. My first Walleye ever through the iceâ€¦  I took these pictures tonight of my boys out their trying their luck. They didnâ€™t catch anything but had a great time watching other people bring in their catches.     I can not believe the thrill of watching a fish come up to your lure and actually getting it on the ice. Cheers, Jen

Great report Jen!  (or should I say Bernadette???? haha). Congrats on your first walleye thru the ice.  Must have been a great feeling for you.  I must say it's been great getting to know you through your posts.  It's always a pleasure reading them!
Congrats Jen.Hope there will be many more.
very nice report, thanks for sharing.
what time is dinner?! great fish

Nice un way to go grl! ......Its funny i nearly headed down that way today,  But i was unsure of the ice conditions. So strange seeing people ice fishing there and just up the river in cally D its all open water and there were guy's in the water wading and catching some nice fish from what i could see of shore.  Again grl nice one!
nice fish, thx for sharing.  saw a vex in action this week a great tool, gonna save my pennies.  Greg
Congrats on your first Wall-ice Jen.
Great report and pics!!!  I can't decide if that's a Pickeral or Wall-ice...
Well I would say that "Wall-Ice" is a lot more fitting in this case ...  hehehe
Very nice Jen  Hope to get out there Friday if this rain doesn't screw things up  Cheers  Craig

Looks like I won't get back on the ice till Friday atleast... so I am keeping my fingers crossed as well.  Never know with the weather... it didn't take long for the ice to come back though.  Cheers Jen
WTG Jen, nice fish (and well equipped shelter!)
Well done Jen, thats a nice fish.
Hey congrats Jen, Glad to hear ya got a nice eye through the hard stuff
